268
00:19:01,218 --> 00:19:02,343
Then I'll do it.

269
00:19:12,634 --> 00:19:15,051
If my wish comes true,
I'll treat you to something nice.

270
00:19:15,551 --> 00:19:18,260
You provided the eyelash,
so it's the least I can do.

271
00:19:28,135 --> 00:19:31,093
Mr Ji had a girlfriend?

272
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:38,509
Sorry.

273
00:19:38,634 --> 00:19:42,676
I'm a left-hander,
so we'll probably bump elbows often.

274
00:19:42,884 --> 00:19:46,051
I ask for your understanding in advance.

275
00:19:47,841 --> 00:19:49,633
Oh, I like this song!

276
00:19:50,126 --> 00:19:53,538
Heath Ledger sang this song in a movie.
Have you seen that movie?

277
00:19:53,729 --> 00:19:57,228
I think I have seen it.
What was the title?

278
00:19:57,313 --> 00:19:59,134
Gosh, what was it?

279
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:00,626
I can't remember.

280
00:20:19,599 --> 00:20:23,108
Oh, my! You are such a bad singer!

281
00:20:23,193 --> 00:20:25,605
Hey, it's not that bad.

282
00:20:31,866 --> 00:20:34,262
Hey, stop, stop.

283
00:20:35,047 --> 00:20:37,055
Don't you think I'm quite a good singer?

284
00:20:39,156 --> 00:20:41,259
Stop singing!

285
00:20:42,949 --> 00:20:46,340
Gosh, stop that! Hey, my ears hurt!

286
00:20:46,444 --> 00:20:48,546
I'm crying because I laughed so hard.

287
00:20:48,766 --> 00:20:51,515
Whenever you're feeling down,
I guess I'll sing for you.

288
00:20:52,931 --> 00:20:54,015
Go on, it's late.

289
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,057
Yes, see you.

290
00:20:56,789 --> 00:20:58,973
Aren't you living in number 502?

291
00:20:59,599 --> 00:21:02,231
You have a package from America.

292
00:21:02,316 --> 00:21:03,858
Thank you, I'll stop by to pick it up.

293
00:21:04,432 --> 00:21:07,098
Oh, your girlfriend is very beautiful.

294
00:21:07,807 --> 00:21:09,474
But I'm not his girlfriend...

295
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:12,431
Then are you my boyfriend?

296
00:21:12,515 --> 00:21:15,599
No, that's not what I meant.

297
00:21:16,912 --> 00:21:18,599
Go on home. I'm sure you're tired.

298
00:21:19,171 --> 00:21:22,081
Yes, I'll be going now.

299
00:21:29,891 --> 00:21:30,890
Bye!

300
00:21:31,140 --> 00:21:32,098
Bye.

301
00:21:42,737 --> 00:21:43,945
You're home?

302
00:21:47,153 --> 00:21:48,486
Where are you coming from?

303
00:21:48,570 --> 00:21:50,445
Have you been working out
this whole time?

304
00:21:50,570 --> 00:21:52,903
Did I take that long?

305
00:21:54,223 --> 00:21:55,403
When did you get home?

306
00:21:55,487 --> 00:21:56,779
Right after the work.

307
00:21:56,945 --> 00:21:59,821
Hey, I went to work
and ran into Ji Sungjoon there.

308
00:22:00,612 --> 00:22:03,570
We're not under any deadlines,
but I think he's working weekends.

309
00:22:03,846 --> 00:22:05,138
Oh, really?

310
00:22:08,529 --> 00:22:09,862
I should wash up.

311
00:22:10,862 --> 00:22:12,237
Okay, go ahead!

312
00:22:26,603 --> 00:22:28,603
He's here for the entire year,

313
00:22:28,697 --> 00:22:30,904
but no one knows his real identity.

314
00:22:31,404 --> 00:22:35,902
We just assume
that he's a son of a wealthy family.

315
00:22:35,986 --> 00:22:37,236
Here's the guest arrival list.

316
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:38,779
Yes, thank you.

317
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:41,362
It's you!

318
00:22:42,458 --> 00:22:43,540
Right?

319
00:22:43,632 --> 00:22:45,083
You treated me like
a homeless person the other day!

320
00:22:47,278 --> 00:22:48,611
I'm so sorry about that!

321
00:22:48,695 --> 00:22:50,195
I offended you, didn't I?

322
00:22:51,821 --> 00:22:53,778
Of course, I was really offended.

323
00:22:53,863 --> 00:22:55,471
You thought I was homeless...

324
00:22:57,529 --> 00:23:00,604
But smiling like that while you apologize,

325
00:23:00,689 --> 00:23:02,572
I bet all the other men fall for it.

326
00:23:02,821 --> 00:23:03,695
Sorry?

327
00:23:03,845 --> 00:23:05,597
Because you're lean and pretty.

328
00:23:06,070 --> 00:23:09,821
Well, since you found this for me,
I'll call it even.

329
00:23:11,112 --> 00:23:12,070
Bump!

330
00:23:12,612 --> 00:23:13,528
What?

331
00:23:13,612 --> 00:23:15,570
Fist bump!

332
00:23:18,057 --> 00:23:18,909
Bump.

333
00:23:20,186 --> 00:23:22,923
If we run into each other again,
let's say hello.

334
00:23:23,654 --> 00:23:24,499
High five.

335
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:29,598
See you around.

336
00:23:35,291 --> 00:23:38,267
He doesn't act like he's wealthy.

337
00:23:48,028 --> 00:23:49,237
It's go time!

338
00:23:57,737 --> 00:23:58,570
Support?

339
00:24:08,835 --> 00:24:09,897
How are you?

340
00:24:57,529 --> 00:24:59,529
By any chance, the glass that day...

341
00:25:01,316 --> 00:25:02,274
The glass?

342
00:25:02,359 --> 00:25:03,361
Nothing, never mind.

343
00:25:08,153 --> 00:25:09,278
Glass?

344
00:25:09,570 --> 00:25:12,320
Is he asking me to repay him
for the glass frame?

345
00:25:18,612 --> 00:25:20,278
Where's the puzzle piece?
Why don't I have it?

346
00:25:20,362 --> 00:25:21,695
I had it right here!

347
00:25:26,902 --> 00:25:28,404
Don't tell me that I dropped it then!

348
00:25:38,112 --> 00:25:39,028
Ma'am!

349
00:25:39,153 --> 00:25:40,320
Ma'am!

350
00:25:40,653 --> 00:25:44,112
Have you seen a puzzle piece
on the ground while cleaning up?

351
00:25:44,855 --> 00:25:45,897
A piece of what?

352
00:25:46,153 --> 00:25:47,278
A puzzle piece.

353
00:25:47,487 --> 00:25:53,152
It's about this big,
and shaped like this, and this.

354
00:25:53,237 --> 00:25:58,917
Oh, this big, and shaped like this?

355
00:25:59,002 --> 00:26:02,669
Yes! This big, and shaped like this!
Did you see it?

356
00:26:02,945 --> 00:26:03,864
No, I didn't see it.

357
00:26:04,903 --> 00:26:07,320
What am I going to do? I can't lose that!

358
00:26:19,028 --> 00:26:19,902
What are you doing?

359
00:26:19,986 --> 00:26:21,403
Are you friends with the floor?

360
00:26:21,487 --> 00:26:22,854
No, it's not like that!

361
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:37,529
There it is!

362
00:27:11,324 --> 00:27:12,442
It's dirty down there. Get up.

363
00:27:14,902 --> 00:27:15,779
Yes.

364
00:27:22,862 --> 00:27:23,903
What the...

365
00:27:26,028 --> 00:27:27,028
No, it's nothing.

366
00:27:27,821 --> 00:27:29,151
What am I going to do?

367
00:27:33,737 --> 00:27:35,902
What should I do?
How am I going to retrieve it?

368
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,945
I have to get in there somehow!

369
00:27:38,362 --> 00:27:40,112
Mr Ji Sungjoon, I have a delivery.

370
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:42,819
Is that for Mr Ji Sungjoon?
You can find him in there.

371
00:27:42,903 --> 00:27:44,695
Give that to me!

372
00:27:52,971 --> 00:27:54,679
You have a delivery.

373
00:27:54,779 --> 00:27:55,733
You can leave it there.

374
00:28:03,112 --> 00:28:04,278
Do you have any more business here?

375
00:28:04,529 --> 00:28:06,487
Yes, I do! I've got serious business!

376
00:28:06,903 --> 00:28:09,737
Would you like a cup of coffee?

377
00:28:11,945 --> 00:28:13,223
You've already got one.

378
00:28:14,570 --> 00:28:16,903
Then, I'll leave you alone.

379
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:18,986
Oh, no!

380
00:28:20,945 --> 00:28:23,162
Oh, my, I've dropped it!

381
00:28:38,695 --> 00:28:40,445
-What are you doing?
-My goodness!

382
00:28:45,903 --> 00:28:47,015
I dropped this.

383
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:49,570
Excuse me.

384
00:28:54,112 --> 00:28:55,362
Mr Ji?

385
00:28:59,529 --> 00:29:01,611
Your shoes are a bit dirty,
so would you like me to shine them?

386
00:29:01,695 --> 00:29:03,570
I'm really good at fire-shining shoes.

387
00:29:03,654 --> 00:29:05,278
If you take off your shoes...

388
00:29:06,028 --> 00:29:07,570
I need your approval.

389
00:29:11,237 --> 00:29:14,445
I don't want my shoes that shine.

390
00:29:15,779 --> 00:29:18,445
Hyejin, are you good
at fire-shining shoes?

391
00:29:18,529 --> 00:29:19,945
That's a great skill!

392
00:29:20,445 --> 00:29:22,445
Fire-shine my shoes, too.

393
00:29:23,445 --> 00:29:24,320
What?

394
00:29:24,405 --> 00:29:25,248
Fire-shine.

395
00:29:28,933 --> 00:29:29,849
Oh no!

396
00:29:31,779 --> 00:29:33,070
That was startling.

397
00:29:59,522 --> 00:30:02,272
Wow, Kim Shinhyuk is a certified lunatic.

398
00:30:04,902 --> 00:30:06,653
What are you doing?

399
00:30:06,737 --> 00:30:07,747
Wait, wait.

400
00:30:07,832 --> 00:30:08,843
What are you doing?

401
00:30:10,278 --> 00:30:11,862
This doesn't feel right...

402
00:30:13,903 --> 00:30:17,361
I don't think we're this close.

403
00:30:17,445 --> 00:30:19,320
I was working on a feature
about brotherly affection,

404
00:30:19,404 --> 00:30:22,112
but I have no idea what it is.

405
00:30:22,529 --> 00:30:23,902
But this isn't going to work!

406
00:30:24,153 --> 00:30:26,552
I love women too much
to get to know what it's like.

407
00:30:28,070 --> 00:30:31,278
But I'm willing to try
one more time to make sure.

408
00:30:34,529 --> 00:30:35,394
I'm just joking.

409
00:30:36,487 --> 00:30:38,778
We're not close enough
to play jokes on one another.

410
00:30:38,862 --> 00:30:40,445
-Are you sure?
-Absolutely sure.

411
00:30:41,445 --> 00:30:42,508
That's too bad.

412
00:30:59,601 --> 00:31:00,933
Ta-da. Is this it?

413
00:31:01,195 --> 00:31:02,529
You were looking for this all day.

414
00:31:06,612 --> 00:31:07,570
But...

415
00:31:08,737 --> 00:31:11,195
-how did you...
-Know you were looking for that?

416
00:31:11,529 --> 00:31:14,069
I overheard you talking
to the cleaning lady.

417
00:31:14,153 --> 00:31:17,404
It's about this big,
and shaped like this, and this...

418
00:31:17,986 --> 00:31:23,153
Oh, this big, and shaped this and this?

419
00:31:23,237 --> 00:31:25,616
Yes! This big, and shaped like this!

420
00:31:29,695 --> 00:31:33,112
Are you trying to hide that from Mr Ji?

421
00:31:34,631 --> 00:31:36,798
Jackson, you're his childhood friend...

422
00:31:37,779 --> 00:31:39,320
...and his first love, Kim Hyejin.

423
00:31:39,487 --> 00:31:40,944
Wait, how did you...

424
00:31:41,028 --> 00:31:42,320
How did I know about that?

425
00:31:42,779 --> 00:31:44,194
Hey, Ji Sungjoon!

426
00:31:44,278 --> 00:31:45,404
Ji Sungjoon!

427
00:31:45,695 --> 00:31:47,653
I'm Kim Hyejin.

428
00:31:47,737 --> 00:31:48,818
Kim Hyejin!

429
00:31:48,902 --> 00:31:52,654
Why do you keep telling him your name?

430
00:31:52,821 --> 00:31:54,695
Jackson, he hung up already!

431
00:31:55,112 --> 00:31:58,777
I used to live next door to you,

432
00:31:58,862 --> 00:32:01,278
and we were classmates
in elementary school!

433
00:32:01,612 --> 00:32:04,903
We had our first kiss together.
I'm your first love!

434
00:32:05,821 --> 00:32:07,570
That's me!

435
00:32:07,695 --> 00:32:10,903
It's me, Kim Hyejin! Kim Hyejin!

436
00:32:14,986 --> 00:32:16,320
Got it, punk?

437
00:32:25,821 --> 00:32:29,112
You were talking on the phone
with no one else on the other line!

438
00:32:36,278 --> 00:32:38,779
That hit the spot!

439
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:42,903
I think it's for the best.

440
00:32:44,332 --> 00:32:45,986
I couldn't tell anyone,

441
00:32:46,570 --> 00:32:48,821
and I thought I was going
to suffocate at work!

442
00:32:49,405 --> 00:32:50,489
So it's good that you know.

443
00:32:51,195 --> 00:32:52,821
Why are you acting
like you're someone else?

444
00:32:53,343 --> 00:32:55,839
Because he's your superior
and you're his subordinate?

445
00:32:57,028 --> 00:32:58,083
No.

446
00:33:00,945 --> 00:33:01,862
To be honest,

447
00:33:03,529 --> 00:33:07,570
I'm not attractive like I used to be.

448
00:33:08,404 --> 00:33:12,112
That's why I'm hiding like this.

449
00:33:17,903 --> 00:33:22,737
The Kim Hyejin that Ji Sungjoon
remembers was something else.

450
00:33:23,821 --> 00:33:28,612
She was popular and smart.
She won lots of awards...

451
00:33:29,695 --> 00:33:31,404
and she was loved wherever she went.

452
00:33:32,250 --> 00:33:34,459
Oh, and it may be hard to believe,

453
00:33:34,779 --> 00:33:38,195
but when I was young,
I was really, really pretty.

454
00:33:39,737 --> 00:33:40,903
You still are.

455
00:33:41,195 --> 00:33:42,195
Excuse me?

456
00:33:42,587 --> 00:33:43,976
You're still pretty.

457
00:33:44,070 --> 00:33:44,976
What?

458
00:33:46,584 --> 00:33:48,500
Mr Kim, you're a nice person.

459
00:33:48,695 --> 00:33:50,778
You know how to console people.

460
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:51,986
But I'm telling the truth.

461
00:33:52,070 --> 00:33:53,986
Oh, my! Thank you very much!

462
00:33:55,237 --> 00:33:56,153
Oh, right.

463
00:33:56,445 --> 00:33:59,153
I need to apologize to you.

464
00:34:00,695 --> 00:34:05,278
I'm sorry for the mistake
I made to you last time.

465
00:34:05,737 --> 00:34:07,570
You've made so many mistakes.

466
00:34:07,654 --> 00:34:09,195
I don't know which one
you're referring to.

467
00:34:09,722 --> 00:34:10,639
Well,

468
00:34:11,909 --> 00:34:13,902
for bringing up
your younger sister.

469
00:34:15,278 --> 00:34:18,237
You always seem so relaxed and carefree.

470
00:34:18,695 --> 00:34:21,902
I couldn't imagine you
had a deep scar like that.

471
00:34:23,590 --> 00:34:24,631
I'm sorry again.

472
00:34:24,945 --> 00:34:26,404
It's water under the bridge.

473
00:34:29,779 --> 00:34:30,779
Mr Kim.

474
00:34:31,112 --> 00:34:34,821
You can consider me as
your younger sister from now on.

475
00:34:35,112 --> 00:34:36,653
-What?
-Yes, why not?

476
00:34:36,737 --> 00:34:39,653
I'll treat you like
my older brother from now on!

477
00:34:39,737 --> 00:34:40,945
I'll be your younger sister.

478
00:34:41,404 --> 00:34:42,948
Come on now.

479
00:34:43,876 --> 00:34:45,459
Then can you make me a wrap,
Little Sister?

480
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:47,069
-What?
-A wrap.

481
00:34:47,153 --> 00:34:48,986
I thought you're going to
be my little sister?

482
00:34:50,161 --> 00:34:51,369
Oh, yes.

483
00:34:51,944 --> 00:34:52,840
Big Brother.

484
00:34:54,244 --> 00:34:56,119
-A slice of garlic in there.
-Yes, sir!

485
00:34:56,203 --> 00:34:57,994
-Put a perilla leaf in there.
-Yes, sir!

486
00:34:58,728 --> 00:34:59,935
Don't forget the sauce!

487
00:35:00,019 --> 00:35:00,942
Yes, sir!

488
00:35:08,437 --> 00:35:10,228
Stuff it in my mouth!

489
00:35:20,768 --> 00:35:22,059
Why, what's wrong?

490
00:35:23,026 --> 00:35:24,851
Oh, no!

491
00:35:24,936 --> 00:35:26,311
Seriously?

492
00:35:26,396 --> 00:35:28,646
You had me startled!

493
00:35:43,562 --> 00:35:47,145
But what are you going to do
if Mr Ji recognizes you?

494
00:35:47,639 --> 00:35:49,722
That will never happen.

495
00:35:51,405 --> 00:35:56,903
Sungjoon takes another girl
for his first love.

496
00:35:57,047 --> 00:35:57,889
What?

497
00:35:58,367 --> 00:35:59,297
What are you talking about?

498
00:36:00,103 --> 00:36:03,569
So Mr Ji thinks someone else is you?

499
00:36:04,935 --> 00:36:05,852
Who?

500
00:36:05,936 --> 00:36:07,019
You don't know her.

501
00:36:07,978 --> 00:36:09,186
My avatar.

502
00:36:09,270 --> 00:36:10,394
Avatar?

503
00:36:10,478 --> 00:36:11,854
There's someone else that looks like you?

504
00:36:12,178 --> 00:36:13,163
You can create copies of yourself?

505
00:36:15,270 --> 00:36:16,895
It's a long story.

506
00:36:23,623 --> 00:36:25,122
Maybe he's not coming tonight?

507
00:36:26,645 --> 00:36:27,936
Is he busy with work?

508
00:36:40,395 --> 00:36:46,478
I'm short 40 cents,
so can you give me a discount?

509
00:36:46,563 --> 00:36:48,896
Of course not, what am I thinking?

510
00:36:57,103 --> 00:36:58,503
I'll pay for his as well.

511
00:37:03,228 --> 00:37:05,743
I'm one up on you now.

512
00:37:06,437 --> 00:37:09,728
What? Then how about
you buy me some kimchi, too?

513
00:37:10,770 --> 00:37:11,645
All right?

514
00:37:17,395 --> 00:37:20,728
You could get room service
with a simple phone call at the hotel.

515
00:37:20,813 --> 00:37:22,062
Why are you eating this here?

516
00:37:22,270 --> 00:37:26,395
Cup ramen, eaten right
after you've had a drink.

517
00:37:26,837 --> 00:37:29,913
There's nothing better than that.

518
00:37:36,847 --> 00:37:38,680
Is he really from a wealthy family?

519
00:37:39,812 --> 00:37:41,551
He's too simple of a man.

520
00:37:55,016 --> 00:37:56,061
Awesome.

521
00:37:58,352 --> 00:37:59,257
Hello, my wife!

522
00:37:59,645 --> 00:38:00,770
Wife?

523
00:38:00,854 --> 00:38:01,977
Where are you?

524
00:38:02,061 --> 00:38:04,519
I'm still near the hotel.
I'll be home soon.

525
00:38:04,603 --> 00:38:07,359
Really?
I'm on the bus heading home, too.

526
00:38:07,895 --> 00:38:09,370
Should I get off
so we can go home together?

527
00:38:09,603 --> 00:38:12,103
Okay, come by the hotel.
We'll go home together.

528
00:38:12,895 --> 00:38:13,854
Okay!

529
00:38:17,270 --> 00:38:20,311
I didn't know you swing that way!

530
00:38:20,395 --> 00:38:23,145
Because there are all sorts of people.

531
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:27,182
I respect all kinds of lifestyles.

532
00:38:27,562 --> 00:38:28,935
Swing what way?

533
00:38:31,186 --> 00:38:32,145
What the...

534
00:38:32,353 --> 00:38:33,644
You're mistaken!

535
00:38:33,728 --> 00:38:35,268
This is my roommate.

536
00:38:35,353 --> 00:38:37,770
She's closer than a sister,
my lifelong best friend!

537
00:38:40,425 --> 00:38:42,657
